cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the application of quantum key distribution (QKD) to enhance the privacy and security of networked control systems (NCS). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the impact of QKD on the control performance of NCS, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the key generation and management processes, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the communication protocol, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
